15. Advanced Concepts (For Strong Understanding)
1. Interning
String x = new String("Hello");
String y = x.intern();


This ensures y goes to the String Pool.

2. Why String is final?

So that:

Nobody can override its behavior

String Pool stays safe

Security in applications (passwords, URLs, etc.)

3. String Pool Mechanism
Literal strings reuse memory instead of creating duplicates.

16. Quick Revision Notes

String is a class, not a primitive.
Strings are immutable.
Stored in String Constant Pool when created using " ".
For fast modifications, use StringBuilder/StringBuffer.
Use equals() to compare values.
Common methods: length, charAt, substring, indexOf, startsWith, endsWith.
Important interview topics: palindrome, reverse, anagrams, sliding window problems.